mongoDB command:
‚òòÔ∏è mongod: start the server port :27017
‚òòÔ∏è mongo: lunch the database to the server

1Ô∏è‚É£ use db_name: switch to a db, if the database donsn't exit, the command create one
2Ô∏è‚É£ show dbs: show database exit
3Ô∏è‚É£ show collections: show the collections in database
4Ô∏è‚É£ db.collection_name.insertOne({ , , }): Create a collection example tours
5Ô∏è‚É£ db.collection_name.insertMany([{}, {}]): add many of fil to collection
6Ô∏è‚É£ db.collection_name.find({ filter }): show the content of collection_name
   {price: { $lte: 500 }}: and filter price last then of equal 500
   {price: { $lt: 500 }, rating: { $gte: 4.8 }} : and filter price greter then 500 && rating equal to 4.8
   { $or: [ {price: {$lt: 300}}, {rating: {$gt: 4.8}} ] }: or filter
   {filter}, {name: 1}: show just the id and the name
7Ô∏è‚É£ db.collection_name.updateOne({ name: "name" }, { $set: { price: 597 } }): update a specifique file 
8Ô∏è‚É£ db.tours.updateMany( { price: { $gt: 500 } , rating: { $gte: 4.8 }}, { $set: { premium: true } } ): update a lot of files
9Ô∏è‚É£ db.tours.deleteMany({ rating: { $lte: 4.8 } }): delete data from the file.
